(73, 1, '2018-08-01 10:11:51', '2018-08-01 03:11:51', '<span><strong>Lake Toba</strong> is a large natural lake in Indonesia located in the super volcano caldera. The lake has a length of 100 kilometers (62 miles), a width of 30 kilometers (19 mi), and a depth of 505 meters (1,657 ft). The lake is located in the middle of the northern island of Sumatera with a surface altitude of about 900 meters (2,953 ft). The lake stretches from 2.88 ° N 98.52 ° east to 2,35 ° N 99.1 ° east. It is the largest lake in Indonesia and the largest volcanic lake in the world. [1] Lake Toba is the site of a massive volcano eruption of magnitude VEI 8 around 69,000 to 77,000 years ago [2] [3] [4] which triggered global climate change. The current dating method determined that 74,000 years ago was more accurate. [5] This eruption is the largest explosive eruption on Earth in the last 25 million years. According to the Toba disaster theory, this eruption has a major impact on human populations around the world; the impact of the eruption killed most of the humans living at the time and is believed to cause shrinking populations in central and eastern Africa and India affecting the genetics of human populations around the world up to the present day. [6] Scientists agree that the Toba eruption triggered a volcanic winter that caused a fall in world temperatures between 3 to 5 ° C (5.4 to 9.0 ° F), and up to 15 ° C (27 ° F) in the upper latitudes. Further research on Lake Malawi, Central Africa, found Toba eruption dust, but found no evidence of major climate change in East Africa. [7] On June 18, 2018, the ferry crash occurred on Lake Toba and drowned more than 190 people</span>', 'Lake Toba', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'danau-toba__trashed', '', '', '2018-08-13 15:44:31', '2018-08-13 08:44:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=73', 0, 'post', '', 0),
