(114, 1, '2018-08-01 13:42:45', '2018-08-01 06:42:45', '<p id="tw-target-text" class="tw-data-text tw-ta tw-text-small" dir="ltr" data-placeholder="Terjemahan"><span lang="en"><strong>Ijen Crater</strong> is an acidic crater lake at the top of Mount Ijen with a height of 2,443 meters\r\nabove sea level with a depth of 200 meters lake and a crater\r\narea reaching 5,466 hectares. The crater lake of Ijen is known to be the largest\r\nacidic water lake in the world [1]. Ijen Crater is in the area of ​​Ijen Park Nature Reserve\r\nBondowoso and Banyuwangi regency, East Java. Every morning at around 02:00 to 04:00,\r\naround the crater can be found the phenomenon of blue fire or blue fire, which is the\r\nuniqueness of this place, because the natural scene is only happening in two places\r\nin the world of Iceland and Ijen. From Ijen Crater,\r\nwe can see the other mountain scenery in the Ijen Mountain complex, among them is the peak\r\nof Mount Merapi which is east of Ijen Crater, Mount Raung, Mount Suket, Mount Rante, and so on. To reach the crater of Mount Ijen from Banyuwangi, can use the economy train with the aim of Banyuwangi\r\nand get off at Karangasem Station then ride motorcycle taxi to the District of Licin and Banyusari Village.\r\nFrom Banyusari, the journey continues to Paltuding by riding a truck carrying sulfur or using a bus and get off at Banyuwangi city and then take a motorcycle taxi can go directly to Paltuding or to Banyusari Village but also by using the tariff bus issued will be more expensive. The main gateway to the Ijen Crater Park Nature Reserve is located in Paltuding, which is also a PHPA Post (Forest Protection and Nature Conservation). Alternative route is Bondowoso - Wonosari - Tapen - Sempol - Paltuding. Other facilities that can be enjoyed by visitors include cottage tours and stalls that sell climbing purposes to witness the beauty of Ijen crater. From Paltuding walk with distance about 3 km. The initial trajectory as far as 1.5 km is quite heavy due to uphill. Most of the tracks are with a 25-35 degree slope. In addition to climbing, the soil structure is also sandy so that increasing the weight of footsteps because it must hold the weight so as not to slide back. After resting at Pos Bunder (a post that is unique because it has a circular shape), the next lane is relatively gentle, but tourists / climbers are treated to a beautiful view of the mountain range. To go down to the crater must cross the rocky terrain as far as 250 meters with a steep condition.</span></p>', 'Ijen Crater', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'ijen-crater__trashed', '', '', '2018-08-13 15:44:13', '2018-08-13 08:44:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=114', 0, 'post', '', 0),
