(122, 1, '2018-08-01 15:01:33', '2018-08-01 08:01:33', '<strong>Siung Beach</strong> is a coastal tourist attraction located in the district. Tepus, precisely located in Wates Village, Purwodadi Village, Tepus Subdistrict, Gunungkidul Regency, Yogyakarta Special Province. The location is approximately 77 km from the city of Yogya and has a tourist adventure location rock climbing with 250 international standard lanes.\r\n\r\nAlong the way to the location of the beach, you will be treated to views of limestone hills overgrown with teak trees. The winding and rising road is a challenge that you must pass before reaching Siung Beach. However, the exhausting journey will pay off when you are already in Siung Beach area. Beach with white sand and the sound of waves, will make your mood and mind calm and peaceful.\r\n\r\nBecause this beach is very remote, facilities available mash is very minimal, only available parking area, toilets, and stalls. For hotel accommodation is not available here, but if you want to spend the night in Siung Beach, you can use the climber hut which looks like a house of stilt with a capacity of approximately 20 people. If you want to spend the night with the natural atmosphere, you can bring your own tent that you can use around the cliffs.\r\n\r\nIf you are from Yogyakarta City, you can use the Yogyakarta-Wonosari-Tepus-Purwodadi-Siung Beach. If you use public transportation, you can use the bus from Giwangan Bus Station Yogyakarta by using the bus Jogja-Wonosari direction. Arrive at Wonosari terminal, you can use public transportation Wonosari-Tepus department. Arriving terminal Tepus, you can use the motorcycle taxi service, because it''s only public transportation that can be used up to Siung Beach.', 'Siung Beach', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'siung-beach__trashed', '', '', '2018-08-13 15:44:04', '2018-08-13 08:44:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=122', 0, 'post', '', 0),
